| Code to clarify how catch and throw actually work. This was used to
| prototype the current (as of commit a4ca26f792d4) implementations of
| catch and throw.

variable bogosity  z" awful" bogosity !

| Print the IP and current silly word.
: .bogus
   cr  r@ cell/ u. bogosity @ count type space ;

| You can easily change throw to unthrow to see what happens and how the
| behavior differs.

: unthrow  drop ;

| If things are working correctly, the calls to .bogus after throw and
| after aa should *not* get executed.
|
| By changing throw to unthrow you can see what would have happened without
| the short-circuting effect of the exception.

: aa  bogosity preserve  z" tremendous"  bogosity !  .bogus  z" oopsie" throw  .bogus ;
: bb  bogosity preserve  z" spectacular"  bogosity !  .bogus  aa  .bogus ;
: cc  .bogus  catch bb  .bogus ;

| Nested load for testing the correct capture of file names and line
| numbers where errors occur.
ld test/exceptions2.mu4

| Test catching an i/o exception.
: ll  catch load-file ;

| Actually, here is a totally generic catch:
: caught  ( cfa)  catch execute ;

hex
z" foobar" ll     | leaves the zstring on the stack, below the error
cc

| ?error will print out each error.
